article.headline: Drake 74, Indiana State 69 (OT)
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Indiana State's Eric Gray scored a game-high 29 points but it wasn't enough as Drake beat the Sycamores 74-69 in overtime Thursday night. The Sycamores had only two players in double figures, compared with four for the Bulldogs (4-5, 1-1 Missouri Valley Conference). Pete Eggers scored 17 points, including 7-of-8 free-point shooting. Klayton Korver had 12, including 4-of-4 from the line, and Aliou Keita and Chris Bryant each added 11 for Drake. Besides Gray, the only other Sycamore in double figures was Tyson Schnitker with 15. Drake shot 15-of-20 during the first half to take a 35-30 lead at the break, but Indiana State (5-7, 0-1) outscored the Bulldogs 33-28 in the second half to force overtime. The Sycamores shot only 32 percent overall while the Bulldogs finished at 69 percent. Indiana State had more points off turnovers (22) than Drake (6), but the Bulldogs outscored the Sycamores 28-12 in the paint.
